1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:15,960
That there are a lot of deleted words hanging in cyberspace right now, because I was trying repeatedly to be more clever than God, and failing again and again and again.

2
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:36,280
And through this wrestling, what I came up with was just a simple truth, and that is that I cannot be more profound than the Word of God, that I shouldn't even dare to try to be more profound.

3
00:00:36,380 --> 00:00:43,300
So what I'm giving you today is like the Alpha Course. It's bare bones Bible, bare bones Christianity.

4
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:56,280
I want to keep things purposefully simple this morning, because I think sometimes in the simplest truths are the most profound truths.

5
00:00:59,830 --> 00:01:08,160
I want to take stock this morning, because that's generally what you do at the end of the calendar year, correct?

6
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:16,430
you take stock of your life. You ask yourself questions like, what have I accomplished? What

7
00:01:16,430 --> 00:01:25,140
did I lack? Or what did I do really well? Did I love well? Or did I hurt? Or did I inadvertently

8
00:01:25,140 --> 00:01:36,880
overlook my fellow, my brothers and sisters? What have I gained? And the contrary, what have I

9
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:46,710
lost sight of in 2002. And here's the big one. Here's the question that within it holds all

10
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:56,880
lesser questions. What is important? What is really non-negotiable? And what that we describe

11
00:01:56,880 --> 00:02:07,910
as important and non-negotiable did I hit or did I miss in 2002? These kind of questions can apply

12
00:02:07,910 --> 00:02:10,910
to an individual's life, like mine or yours.

13
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:15,240
They can apply to a business. They can apply to a family.

14
00:02:17,290 --> 00:02:21,210
I, for example, have found myself wondering whether or not the

15
00:02:21,210 --> 00:02:25,350
hours that I've pulled at work or at school really were the best

16
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:29,580
thing for my family in 2002. And actually,

17
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:33,160
I'm not really wondering about this question anymore because my wife,

18
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:37,460
the executor of our household, has spoken very clearly on this

19
00:02:37,460 --> 00:02:50,460
matter. That's right. And you can probably guess what her opinion is. And here's the, here's the

20
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:57,500
clincher. This is what, something you probably knew was coming. How are we, this family of Christ

21
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:08,890
followers, doing? What kind of stock do we take of ourselves at the end of 2002? Now, don't be afraid.

22
00:03:09,370 --> 00:03:11,290
Don't be nervous about what's coming next.

23
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:19,230
I do not have any hard and fast assessment of Fullerton First Baptist outlined neatly on page three of my notes, okay?

24
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:22,210
Nothing like that is coming your way this morning.

25
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:26,410
Because I don't presume to know that much.

26
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:36,810
Taking stock of the church, of a family like ours, is a bigger question than one I can answer.

27
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:39,210
It's bigger than Kirk.

28
00:03:39,210 --> 00:03:44,470
It's bigger than the whole pastoral staff combined, all the boards, the trustees.

29
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:52,760
In fact, I venture to say that that question is bigger than the weight of every person in this church's opinion.

30
00:03:55,090 --> 00:04:01,370
God alone has a fair idea of how we've done in 2002.

31
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:09,190
And the best that I think you and I can do is prayerfully ask him to share it with us.

32
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:16,780
So as I said, this morning is no State of the Union address.

33
00:04:19,010 --> 00:04:20,130
Try not to act too disappointed.

34
00:04:22,210 --> 00:04:28,310
All I have this morning is the same question that we ask ourselves individually at the end of every year.

35
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:31,680
What is truly important?

36
00:04:34,180 --> 00:04:38,520
What is non-negotiable in the life of Fullerton First Baptist Church?

37
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,280
Here's a hint.

38
00:04:43,530 --> 00:04:46,890
It's not well-manicured programming for 2003.

39
00:04:46,890 --> 00:04:53,130
It's a command from our boss, from the Lord Jesus himself

40
00:04:53,130 --> 00:04:57,480
He says it, he says a new command I give you

41
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:01,610
Love one another, as I have loved you

42
00:05:01,610 --> 00:05:06,560
So you must love one another, by this everyone will know

43
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:10,560
That you are my disciples, if you love

44
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:17,430
One another, I think it's kind of sad how a statement like this

45
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:21,430
Which is so simple and so profound gets buried in our culture

46
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:26,320
by a thousand clichés and bad love songs.

47
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:30,300
I mean, for those of you who have seen Moulin Rouge!

48
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,580
and those of you who haven't,

49
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:35,500
and by the way, I recommend that you see Moulin Rouge!

50
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,880
You know the litany of clichés.

51
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:40,260
Love is like oxygen.

52
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:43,540
Love is a many-splendored thing.

53
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:45,740
Love lifts us up where we belong.

54
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,020
All you need is love.

55
00:05:49,710 --> 00:05:54,280
What the world needs now is love, sweet love.

56
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:57,620
It's the only thing that the world has just too little of.

57
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:59,780
Blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

58
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:04,140
We misuse this word so much.

59
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:06,440
We trivialize it so much.

60
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:12,900
It gets so small that we forget how profound this simple four-letter word is.

61
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:15,650
Let's recapture it.

62
00:06:17,370 --> 00:06:20,890
Here's love once again in the words of the Master.

63
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,800
My command is this.

64
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:31,940
Love each other as I, I, the Lord Jesus Christ, have loved you.

65
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:38,400
Greater love has no man than this, that he lay down his life for his friends.

66
00:06:40,030 --> 00:06:41,650
If you are my friends, do what I command.

67
00:06:42,090 --> 00:06:42,950
This is my command.

68
00:06:43,940 --> 00:06:45,620
Love each other.

69
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,760
You see, love is not a cliche.

70
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:55,790
Love is not a mushy fluff of sentimentality.

71
00:06:56,890 --> 00:06:57,890
It's not a song lyric.

72
00:06:58,050 --> 00:07:00,190
It's not, you know, a hormone imbalance.

73
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,220
Love, in Christ's eyes, is an absolute necessity.

74
00:07:05,620 --> 00:07:06,120
It's a command.

75
00:07:07,710 --> 00:07:15,230
It's one of those non-negotiables that come too easily to us every New Year's Day when we make our resolutions.

76
00:07:16,010 --> 00:07:19,520
Love is Christ's non-negotiable.

77
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:28,300
See, in its pure form, love is a state of complete self-giving.

78
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:34,810
It's literally to die for the object of your love.

79
00:07:37,570 --> 00:07:41,130
See, when people describe feelings of being in love,

80
00:07:42,490 --> 00:07:46,930
they attach it to how that other person makes them feel.

81
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:50,490
Usually, how that other person makes them feel about themselves.

82
00:07:52,450 --> 00:07:57,330
They feel exhilarated, they feel flushed, they feel proud, they feel ten feet tall.

83
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:58,170
Pick one.

84
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:03,980
And there's nothing wrong or even cheap about this kind of romantic love.

85
00:08:03,980 --> 00:08:10,340
The kind of love that gets popularized in our society, however,

86
00:08:10,340 --> 00:08:15,090
is not primarily what Jesus Christ is talking about.

87
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:26,200
Love in Christ's terms doesn't mean what another person does for you.

88
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:31,980
Love in Christ's terms means what you are prepared to do

89
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:36,640
for that other person that you say you love.

90
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:44,480
And neither is love some kind of hippy-trippy idealism,

91
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:48,000
you know, where people gather around a campfire and play a guitar

92
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,400
and share intense, warm feelings.

93
00:08:51,000 --> 00:09:00,100
about one another. If love has intensity, it is intense concern for another expressed in actions,

94
00:09:01,540 --> 00:09:09,080
not song, not words, or let not song and words alone. I said earlier that the most important

95
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:17,240
thing in the life of our church, of any church, of any family, was not well-manicured programming

96
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:24,990
for 2003. Perhaps what I should have said is this, the most important thing in the life of our church

97
00:09:24,990 --> 00:09:28,970
is evidence of our intense love in action.

98
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,580
In other words, if it's for love's sake,

99
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:38,650
for the love of people of this community, for example,

100
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:43,180
the love of people outside this family of faith,

101
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:49,960
that we plan and we labor and we dream about programming in 2003,

102
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:53,840
then our motivations are right.

103
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:56,360
Then our motivations are love.

104
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:01,810
And chances are, if our motivations are right,

105
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:06,230
then our programs born out of that motivation are also right.

106
00:10:09,260 --> 00:10:10,340
I think of kids' play.

107
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,380
I mentioned this earlier during the announcements.

108
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:17,800
Kids' play is an intense labor of love.

109
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:24,170
But see, the love wasn't for the planning itself.

110
00:10:24,970 --> 00:10:26,150
Maybe some people enjoyed it.

111
00:10:26,230 --> 00:10:27,410
I personally wouldn't.

112
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:31,090
And love wasn't for the sport of basketball itself,

113
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:33,760
though some people enjoy that too.

114
00:10:34,140 --> 00:10:39,090
The labor of love of a program like kids' play

115
00:10:39,090 --> 00:10:46,210
comes from a deeper sort of self-sacrificing desire to see children and through these children

116
00:10:46,210 --> 00:10:55,260
their families be exposed to the sacrificial love of Christ and that love gets expressed

117
00:10:55,260 --> 00:11:03,420
not through the program of kids play primarily but through the program of our hearts through us

118
00:11:03,420 --> 00:11:11,910
you see above and beyond programming my friends and worship and preaching and all the labors of

119
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:21,390
love that take place here on a week-in, week-out basis is the matter of our character as a people

120
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:30,220
of Christ. An author, Donald, I can never say this word right, Potersky, puts it this way,

121
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:37,740
the world needs to see what the Christian life looks like. People who think God is unnecessary

122
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:45,810
or just optional in life need fresh images of how life is meant to be lived. They need hard

123
00:11:45,810 --> 00:11:50,760
evidence that following Jesus really makes a difference. In order

124
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:54,220
to engage in today's world with a credible

125
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:58,820
Christianity, contemporary followers of Jesus

126
00:11:58,820 --> 00:12:03,100
need to be strategic, injecting fresh meaning into

127
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:07,400
an old gospel will not be achieved by

128
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:11,600
buying more primetime television slots or by handing out

129
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:16,020
colored tracks. Rather, the gospel will be perceived as

130
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:23,920
a feasible alternative when those who do not know God have some positive personal experiences

131
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:36,860
with people who do know him. And that's the bottom line, isn't it? That's the good news

132
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:44,010
and the bad news all wrapped into one. We are, all of us, the ones that draw or repel

133
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:53,440
people from Christ inside this church, outside this church. It's us. It's been said that

134
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:58,720
the greatest single cause of atheism in the world today is Christians who honor Jesus with their

135
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:05,290
lips, but then walk out the door and do not honor him with their lifestyle. That is what an

136
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:27,510
unbelieving world simply finds unbelievable. The Bible says it even better, as usual. Paul, the

137
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:33,720
author of what we, you know, of the New Testament, of most of the New Testament rather, writes about

138
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:38,680
the non-negotiable character of love in his famous love chapter, the one that we use at weddings

139
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:44,060
all the time? I'll read it. And now I will show you

140
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:47,520
the most excellent way. If I speak in the tongue of men and angels

141
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:52,260
but have not love, I'm only a resounding gong or

142
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:56,490
a clanging cymbal. If I have the gift of prophecy and can

143
00:13:56,490 --> 00:14:00,390
fathom all mysteries and all knowledge, and if I have

144
00:14:00,390 --> 00:14:04,130
faith that can move mountains but have not love, I'm nothing.

145
00:14:05,060 --> 00:14:08,880
If I give all I possess to the poor and surrender my body

146
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:21,000
to the flames, but have not love, I've gained nothing. Love is patient. Love is kind. It does

147
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:28,310
not envy. It does not boast. It is not proud. It is not rude. It is not self-seeking. It is not

148
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:37,560
easily angered. It keeps no record of wrongs. Love does not delight in evil, but always rejoices with

149
00:14:37,560 --> 00:14:49,670
the truth it always protects it always trusts it always hopes it always perseveres love never fails

150
00:14:49,670 --> 00:14:55,750
but where there are prophecies they'll cease and where there are tongues they'll be stilled where

151
00:14:55,750 --> 00:15:08,200
there is knowledge it will pass away for we know in part and we prophesy in part but when perfection

152
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:11,590
comes. The imperfect disappears.

153
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:16,640
When I was a child, I talked like a child. I thought like a child. I

154
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:21,860
reasoned like a child. But when I became a man,

155
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:26,930
I put childish ways behind me. Now we

156
00:15:26,930 --> 00:15:30,990
see but a poor reflection as in a mirror. Then we shall see

157
00:15:30,990 --> 00:15:33,990
face to face. Now I know in part.

158
00:15:34,970 --> 00:15:39,770
Then I shall know fully, even as I am fully known.

159
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:46,040
And now these three remain, faith, hope, and love.

160
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:49,540
But the greatest of these is love.

161
00:15:54,590 --> 00:16:00,730
You see, these verses, they hold the non-negotiable that is our focus this morning.

162
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:07,910
We can program and we can plan and we can spend and we can spruce up this facility,

163
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:14,570
which we have, by the way, until it fairly shines with spit and polish and professionalism.

164
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:20,140
You can listen to the finest music coming from this stage.

165
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:26,250
You can learn from the most inspirational and well-crafted sermons.

166
00:16:28,630 --> 00:16:29,770
We can have great video.

167
00:16:29,970 --> 00:16:31,050
We can have great audio.

168
00:16:31,310 --> 00:16:33,770
We can have graphics and lights.

169
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:37,140
And all that stuff can hit new professional heights.

170
00:16:37,540 --> 00:16:40,760
And it probably will in this next year.

171
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:53,030
But it doesn't amount to much if our character, if our love doesn't match up with the program.

172
00:16:53,530 --> 00:16:58,580
with the message. It doesn't matter how polished we make it.

173
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:04,540
You might paraphrase verses 1 through 3 in 1 Corinthians

174
00:17:04,540 --> 00:17:08,420
chapter 13 like this. If our sermons bring down

175
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:12,460
the house every Sunday morning, and we have no love for those that need to

176
00:17:12,460 --> 00:17:16,400
hear this solid teaching for perhaps the first time,

177
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:21,630
then we're preaching to the choir. If we play and sing

178
00:17:21,630 --> 00:17:26,240
like the New York Philharmonic, if our visuals give Madison Avenue

179
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:34,560
will run for its money, and the best we can do is congratulate ourselves on our musical or our

180
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:44,790
aesthetic or our technical slickness, then we've really accomplished nothing. If we pack this place

181
00:17:44,790 --> 00:17:49,730
to the gills with looky-loos and people looking only for the big show, if we're the hottest

182
00:17:49,730 --> 00:17:59,190
Christian ticket in Fullerton, California, but our lives are not filled with God's love, the kind of

183
00:17:59,190 --> 00:18:09,100
love that could take or leave all that stuff, then we'll attract fellow spectators to this place.

184
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:19,630
But we won't see God change many lives in our midst, because if we don't have love, our own

185
00:18:19,630 --> 00:18:30,070
lives aren't changed much, and the world at large will see it. They'll know it. Sunday morning matters,

186
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:37,560
absolutely. The worship matters, absolutely. The sermon should always be thoughtful and heartfelt,

187
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:41,480
but when is Kirk not thoughtful or heartfelt?

188
00:18:45,670 --> 00:18:47,230
The worship should be inspirational.

189
00:18:48,580 --> 00:18:49,400
But I'll say it again.

190
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:52,700
If our hopes are pinned on musical spectacles

191
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:55,080
or the celebrity in the pulpit

192
00:18:55,080 --> 00:19:00,520
and we're relying on that to make a difference,

193
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:03,060
to transfigure Fullerton First Baptist,

194
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:07,980
then we're being naive and our priorities are skewed.

195
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:10,670
I don't think that's the case this morning.

196
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,100
Among all of you, I've found intense love.

197
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:17,300
It's the reason I came. It's the reason my family has stayed.

198
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:22,260
And I guess I say all of this to encourage you,

199
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:24,680
whether or not you're part of what goes on up here,

200
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,660
your character matters.

201
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,800
Someone will come to hear great worship.

202
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:33,820
Someone will come to be taught and inspired.

203
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:36,600
Someone will stay because of you.

204
00:19:36,980 --> 00:19:45,260
Because the most lasting reason for a person to want God

205
00:19:45,260 --> 00:19:48,490
and to find God in our midst,

206
00:19:48,490 --> 00:19:51,960
to become a part of this family, this body of believers,

207
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:57,540
is the character and love exhibited by you.

208
00:19:58,350 --> 00:19:59,930
By all of us, I should say.

209
00:20:02,490 --> 00:20:05,550
And that's inside this place, and that is outside this place.

210
00:20:05,810 --> 00:20:11,090
I'm going to put it really simply.

211
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:13,240
Really simply.

212
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:16,960
We are the message.

213
00:20:26,140 --> 00:20:31,580
I guess all of this amounts really to just a kind of a long thank you this morning.

214
00:20:32,820 --> 00:20:36,960
2002 has been a year of incredible building, incredible sacrifice,

215
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:45,850
and I think through it all, one of just incredible affection shown one to another.

216
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:49,160
And that is where our hope should lie.

217
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:51,760
People will see your warmth.

218
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:55,760
People will see your love, your self-sacrificing love,

219
00:20:55,960 --> 00:21:00,920
and in that, they will see a little glimpse of Christ's love for them.

220
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:05,780
Jesus said it, greater love has no one.

221
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:08,900
than the person who lays down his life for his friends.

222
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:13,530
Jesus laid down his life for us.

223
00:21:14,510 --> 00:21:16,270
And people's first glimpse of that

224
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:22,190
is not going to be some philosophical treatise.

225
00:21:23,170 --> 00:21:27,310
It's going to be you, in your school, in your work,

226
00:21:27,430 --> 00:21:30,360
in your home, in the shopping center.

227
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:35,710
That's where my hope is for 2003.

228
00:21:36,410 --> 00:21:42,490
In you. Pray with me.

